### Notes

*   Applications that do not correctly handle environment variables exceeding 128 characters include [CadStar PCB](/CadStar_PCB), Checkit, Computer Select CD-ROM, RenderMan, [VINES Network](/VINES_Network), [Windows 3.0](/Windows_3.0), and [Word for Windows 6.0](/Word_for_Windows_6.0).
*   [4DOS](/4DOS) and [MS-DOS 7.0](/MS-DOS_7.0) set the length to 127 and insert [ASCII-13](/ASCII_13) at that position. [Borland](/Borland) libraries may set the length to 128 without the ASCII-13. For shorter command lines, 4DOS/[NDOS](/NDOS) and [DR-DOS](/DR-DOS) also insert an [ASCII-0](/ASCII_0) after the ASCII-13, but not when invoked via the [INSTALL](/INSTALL_(CONFIG.SYS_directive)) directive; MS-DOS does not.

